# Discord ↔ HQ ↔ Ashed — identity and auth layers

**Do not conflate identities.** Each layer answers a different question. Mixing them causes wrong tenant data, false owner checks, or Ashed JWT scope leaks.

## Identity graph

```
Discord User (snowflake)
  │
  ├─ discord_member_links ──► Alliance A × Member M0
  │                        └► Alliance A × Member M1   (multi-character: many rows per Discord user per alliance)
  │                        └► Alliance B × Member M0   (different guild / alliance)
  │
  └─ discord_user_prefs (locale only — not auth)

HQ User (hq_users.id, email, optional ashedUserId)
  │
  ├─ alliance_memberships ──► HQ RBAC (owner / maintainer / viewer) on web
  └─ MAY correspond to an Ashed seat — not required for Discord bot use

Ashed (source of truth for roster + alliance ownership on ashed.online)
  │
  ├─ Member roster (who is in the alliance in-game)
  ├─ owner_id / owner_email / collaborators on alliance row
  └─ Paid seat / JWT — used by HQ web connect and per-alliance bot credentials
```

| Identity | Stored in | Used for |
| --- | --- | --- |
| **Discord user** | Discord platform | Who invoked a slash command or button |
| **Member link** | `discord_member_links` | Which **in-game character** this Discord user acts as **in one HQ alliance** |
| **HQ user** | `hq_users` + session | Web UI, RBAC, connect/settings sync |
| **Ashed seat** | Ashed JWT / connection string | Proving access to Ashed API; owner vs maintainer on alliance list |
| **HQ alliance tenant** | `alliances` + `discord_guild_alliances` | Scoping all bot + VR data to one alliance per Discord guild |

**Key invariant:** Bot member commands still act as **`discord_user_id` + `discord_member_links`**. When `discord_hq_links` exists, HQ web commanders (`hq_member_links`) are **mirrored** into `discord_member_links` (on `/link`, on web member-link, and lazily on `/vr` / help / officer gates) so users do not re-enter name+UID on Discord. Inheritance never steals a commander already linked to another Discord user.

## Runtime layers

```
Discord client
    │  slash / button (guild_id, discord user id)
    v
HQ Discord webhook  — verify DISCORD_PUBLIC_KEY; ephemeral for secrets
    │  resolveAllianceForGuild(guild_id) → alliances.id
    v
HQ bot service      — command handlers, pending state, audit, i18n
    │  member reads: loadAllianceMembersForBot(allianceId) ONLY
    v
Ashed API           — roster / alliance list (read-only on bot paths)

HQ Web (separate entry)
    │  session + requireSessionPermission / alliance from session
    v
HQ BFF routes       — may use user's Ashed JWT from connect flow
    v
Ashed API           — sync roles, settings, admin surfaces

HQ cron / internal  — CRON_SECRET / VR_DAILY_REPORT_SECRET / service tokens
    │  no Discord user; alliance resolved from config or guild registry
    v
HQ jobs             — reports, season sync, future quick-task backends
```

When adding features, name which **entry layer** you are in and which **identity** you authenticate.

## What each proof establishes

| Capability | Must prove | How (today) | Grants |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| **Member bot commands** (`/link-commander`, `/link-last-war-profile`, `/vr`, `/immunity`) | Discord user ↔ in-game character in **this guild's alliance** | `/link-commander` name+UID, **or** inherit from `hq_member_links` once `discord_hq_links` exists | Act as that **member** for VR stats |
| **HQ account link** (`/link`) | Discord user ↔ **HQ user** | `/link` → browser OAuth (`user_link` nonce) → `discord_hq_links`; then inherit web commanders into `discord_member_links` | Prerequisite for `/link-ashed`; also unlocks inherited commanders for bot commands |
| **Guild registration** (`/link-alliance`) | Same Discord user is **alliance owner in-game** | `/link-commander` member link where `linked.ashedMemberId === alliances.ownerMemberExternalId` (`callerIsAllianceOwner`), or platform maintainer | Bind `discord_guild_alliances` |
| **Alliance credentials** (`/link-ashed`) | Caller holds **Ashed owner JWT** for tag (optional) | `verifyBase44Connection` + `filterAccessibleAlliances` owner role + tag match | `alliance_ashed_credentials`; enables bot roster reads + Ashed tools — **not required for auth** |
| **HQ web admin** | Signed-in **HQ user** with RBAC on alliance | Session + `requireSessionPermission` / alliance membership | Web mutations, trains, admin — **not** automatic Discord bot power |
| **Cron / internal report** | Service secret + configured alliance | Bearer token; `resolveAllianceForGuild` or explicit alliance config | Read/write **without** Discord actor |

**Member proof ≠ owner proof.** Linked as a roster member does not imply owner. Owner bot commands must call explicit owner checks (`callerIsAllianceOwner` or Ashed owner JWT path).

**Owner proof ≠ HQ maintainer.** Ashed collaborator / HQ maintainer must not bypass owner-only bot setup unless product explicitly adds that path.

## `/link-commander` and multi-character

Target model (see multi-link migration):

- **One Discord user → many `discord_member_links` rows per alliance** (unique on `(alliance_id, discord_user_id, ashed_member_id)`).
- **One in-game member → one Discord user per alliance** (unique on `(alliance_id, ashed_member_id)`).
- **`/link-commander`** or **`/link-last-war-profile`** adds or updates a character; **`replace:true`** replaces all links with one; **`/unlink`** removes a row.
- **`/link`** binds Discord ↔ HQ account only (`discord_hq_links`) — never name + UID.
- **Character-scoped commands** (`/vr`, `/immunity`, future quick tasks): if `listDiscordLinksForUser` returns **> 1**, prompt **Which character?** (button picker bound to `linkId` / `ashedMemberId`). Never apply an action without a resolved link row.

`/help` (`resolveDiscordBotUserContext`) should reflect: guild registered?, credentials present?, link count, owner vs member — not a single generic message.

## Ashed as source of truth

- **Roster** (member ids, names, former status): Ashed via alliance-scoped JWT — **bot entry:** `loadAllianceMembersForBot` only.
- **Alliance owner:** `alliances.ownerAshedUserId` / `ownerEmail` synced from Ashed on connect/sync; bot owner checks use linked member id against these fields.
- **In-game facts** (UID, display name for link verification): Last War THP lookup + Ashed roster cross-check — HQ DB does not invent members.
- **VR season / stats:** HQ-local (`member_season_vr`, game-season helpers) — not written back to Ashed by the bot.

**Credential resolution order:** `alliance_ashed_credentials` for `allianceId` → legacy `VR_BOT_ASHED_BEARER_TOKEN` **only** if `alliances.tag` matches `VR_BOT_ASHED_ALLIANCE_TAG`. Never use alliance A's token to read alliance B.

**Bot paths stay read-only on Ashed.** Do not add mutating Ashed calls from Discord handlers unless a future feature has explicit owner JWT + audit + idempotency design.

## Tag-only UX

User-facing bot copy and command options use **`alliances.tag`** only. Internal FK writes use `alliances.id`. Never expose nanoid or Ashed hex ids in Discord replies.

## Secrets and audit

- `/link-with-authentication` and any future JWT intake: **ephemeral** Discord responses; redact keys in `discord_bot_audit`.
- Discord verifies **interaction signature**, not alliance ownership — ownership is always proven inside the handler after tenant resolution.

## Future: quick tasks, cron, HQ web triggers

When extending the bot or job system, **reuse layers** — do not invent a fourth auth shortcut.

| Trigger | Actor identity | Alliance scope | Typical pattern |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| **Discord slash** | `discord_user_id` + resolved **member link** (or owner check) | `resolveAllianceForGuild(guild_id)` | Handler in `src/lib/vr/` + webhook route |
| **Discord cron post** (daily VR report) | None (service) | Guild registry or env fallback | `src/app/api/internal/vr/daily-report` + `CRON_SECRET` |
| **HQ web button** | `session.hqUserId` + RBAC permission | Session alliance | API route → enqueue or call shared server function |
| **Future bot “quick task”** | Same as slash — **must pick link** if multi-character | Same guild tenant | New handler; same `loadAllianceMembersForBot` + link resolution |

Shared job helpers should accept explicit context, e.g. `{ allianceId, trigger: 'discord' | 'cron' | 'web', discordUserId?, linkId?, hqUserId? }` and enforce the matching proof for that trigger. **Cron and web must not impersonate a Discord user** without a documented, audited break-glass path.

Prefer **one implementation** for business logic (report build, season resolve, entitlement checks) invoked from bot, cron, and web — with **auth at the entry boundary** only.

## Ashed is optional for auth

Ashed credentials are **never** required to complete member link, Discord onboarding, or guild registration. They are an optional follow-up for Ashed-powered tools (roster sync, iframe, video processing with role, bot credential reads). See [`.cursor/rules/ashed-optional-auth.mdc`](ashed-optional-auth.mdc).

